#!/bin/sh

# disable CTRL-C
trap "" 2

cat<<EOF

WELCOME TO TARGET DISPLAY MODE
 ______________________________


You can use "hotkeys" or CLI commands to control this system.

+-----------------------+---------------+--------------------------------------+
| Hotkey*               | CLI Command   |                                      |
+-----------------------+---------------+--------------------------------------+
| ALT+F1, press <ENTER> | n/a           | Bring up the system default console) |
+-----------------------+---------------+--------------------------------------+
| ALT+F2, press <ENTER> | tdm_toggle    | Toggle Target Display Mode ON or OFF |
+-----------------------+---------------+--------------------------------------+
| ALT+F3, press <ENTER> | tdm_on        | Turn Target Display Mode ON          |
+-----------------------+---------------+--------------------------------------+
| ALT+F4, press <ENTER> | tdm_off       | Turn Target Display Mode OFF         |
+-----------------------+---------------+--------------------------------------+
| ALT+F5, press <ENTER> | tdm_shutdown  | Shutdown and power-off the iMac      |
+-----------------------+---------------+--------------------------------------+


*) Depending on your Keyboard layout, you must use ALT+(Fn key)+F1, etc.

EOF


